This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with person re-identification using a multi-branch network architecture. It also involves deep learning techniques for feature extraction, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper uses popular person re-identification datasets, which could fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for training the network, which could also fall under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
